<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="649" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[745,1341,1652,2080]" pageId="30" pageNumber="649">
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. S. Miller" authorityYear="1902" box="[749,1002,1771,1804]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Chaerephon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="649" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">Chaerephon pusillus</taxonomicName>
was previously included in 
<taxonomicName box="[783,919,1810,1843]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Chaerephon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="649" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pumilus">C. pumilus</taxonomicName>
, but studies by S. M. Goodman and colleagues in 2007 and 2010 showedit to be much smaller, and to be distinct on molecular grounds. An endemic species of hemipteran ectoparasite, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jordan" authorityYear="1922" box="[1115,1253,1972,2001]" class="Insecta" family="Polyctenidae" genus="Hypoctenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="649" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hypoctenes</taxonomicName>
hutsoni (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1874" box="[797,982,2012,2041]" class="Insecta" family="Polyctenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="649" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Polyctenidae</taxonomicName>
), occurs only on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. S. Miller" authorityYear="1902" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Chaerephon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="649" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">C. pusillus</taxonomicName>
from Aldabra Atoll. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
